Script to calculate upper-quartile normalized values for an input table.

e.g. of input

	sample	genename	count	type
	smp1	gene1	72	ctrl
	smp1	gene2	6	ctrl
	smp1	gene3	65	ctrl
	smp2	gene21	58	ctrl
	smp2	gene22	64	ctrl
	smp2	gene3	45	ctrl
	smp4	gene21	83	cond
	smp4	gene2	8	cond
	smp4	gene3	76	cond

e.g. of output

	sample	genename	count	type	count.norm
	smp1	gene1	72	ctrl	1.10769230769231
	smp1	gene2	6	ctrl	0.0923076923076923
	smp1	gene3	65	ctrl	1
	smp2	gene21	58	ctrl	1
	smp2	gene22	64	ctrl	1.10344827586207
	smp2	gene3	45	ctrl	0.775862068965517
	smp4	gene21	83	cond	1.12162162162162
	smp4	gene2	8	cond	0.108108108108108
	smp4	gene3	76	cond	1.02702702702703
